      section
        h2 The Wow of Genetic Algorithms
        br
        h3 By Roey Chasman

      section
        h2 What Are Genetic Algorithms?
        br
        p Genetic Algorithms use evolutionary principles to 'evolve' and 'adapt' based on environments to some truth, prediction, or optimization.

      section
        h2 DNA and Genes
        br
        p Genetic Algorithms (GA) are modeled after biological reproduction.
        p They are easy to think about when we use metaphors from occurences in nature.
        ul
          li
          li 'Genes' are a metaphor for features or traits in a problem space.
          li Collectively Genes are referred to as 'DNA'
          li GA's recombinate Genes in DNA to hopefully evolve better and better solutions.
          li Applying GA means carefully selecting the problem features to use in your DNA.

      section
        h2 What's in a GA? Actors
        br
        p Actors what we call individuals within a population.
        ul
          li
          li Actors have their own DNA contributed by their parents or random chance.
          li Actors are evaluated for fitness.
          li Actors breed, some more than others.
          li Actors die..

      section
        h2 What's in a GA? Populations
        br
        ul
          li A Population is a discrete generation of actors.
          li Populations have sizes. Some GA's might use fixed or variable population sizes.
          li The Population or generation size is a critical input to any GA.

      section
        h2 Implementation
        br
        p While not necesarily 'easy' to implement, GA's actually follow a simple series of steps.
        ol
          li I. Genesis
          li II. Fitness
          li III. Reproduction
          li IV. Death

